You are returning a pointer to a local variable of the function. As result the pointer has an invalid value and the program has undefined behavior because the pointed variable is not alive after exiting the function. Its memory can be overwritten by for example the call of `printf`.

To make your program to work define the variable `static`. For example

    int * add( const int *x, const int *y )
    {
        static int c;
    
        c = *x + *y;
    
        return &amp;c;
    }

