IMHO it&#39;s a good idea to validate the string before carrying out the conversion so as to eliminate the worry of generating an exception or, at the very least try to catch the exception and deal with it.

**Validating a Numerical String using the [String#matches()](https://www.tutorialspoint.com/java/java_string_matches.htm) method:**

In this example the [String#matches()](https://www.tutorialspoint.com/java/java_string_matches.htm) method is used along with a [Regular Expression](https://www.vogella.com/tutorials/JavaRegularExpressions/article.html) (RegEx) to validate the fact that the string contained within **roomString[i]** array element is indeed a string representation of a signed or unsigned integer numerical value. If it&#39;s not then an error message is displayed to console and processing continues with the next array element.

